objecttypes.name: Well
objecttypes.description: The origin of a set of wellbores.

objecttypes.name: WellLog
objecttypes.description: A well log is a data type that correlates a particular measurement or multiple measurements in a wellbore against depth and/or time within that wellbore. When plotted visually, well logs are typically long line graphs (called "curves") but may sometimes be discrete points or intervals. This schema object is intended for digital well logs, not raster log files or raster calibration files, but may be used for the latter in the absence of a defined OSDU schema for these use cases.

objecttypes.name: Wellbore
objecttypes.description: A hole in the ground extending from a point at the earth's surface to the maximum point of penetration.

objects.name: ActivityType
objects.description: General method or circumstance of logging - MWD, completion, ...

objects.name: BaseDepth
objects.description: DEPRECATED: populate data.SamplingStart or data.SamplingStop instead, for informational purposes data.BottomMeasuredDepth. SamplingStart and SamplingStop support other domains than depth.

objects.name: Basin
objects.description: A natural geographic area covering a single depositional system.

objects.name: BasinDescription
objects.description: A textual description of the Basin.

objects.name: BasinID
objects.description: Native identifier from a Master Data Management System or other trusted source external to OSDU - stored here in order to allow for multi-system connection and synchronization. If used, the "Source" property should identify that source system.

objects.name: BasinName
objects.description: Name of the Basin.

objects.name: BasinNameAliases
objects.description: DEPRECATED: please use data.NameAliases. Alternative names, including historical, by which this basin is/has been known.

objects.name: BasinTypeID
objects.description: High level classification of the geological characteristics of the Basin; for example, Foothills, Active Margin, Passive Margin, etc.

objects.name: BottomMeasuredDepth
objects.description: Informational Bottom Measured Depth of the Well Log. Always populate SamplingStart and SamplingStop, which represents the real sampling of the WellLog, including  non-depth sampling.

objects.name: CandidateReferenceCurveIDs
objects.description: Secondary index curves, which are alternative candidates to act as ReferenceCurveID. Generally not populated, except in the cases where multiple reference curves are present, e.g. measured depth and time.

objects.name: CompanyID
objects.description: The relationship to company who engaged the service company (ServiceCompanyID) to perform the logging.

objects.name: CurrentOperatorID
objects.description: The current operator organization ID; the organization ID may also be found in the FacilityOperatorOrganisationID of the FacilityOperator array providing the actual dates.

objects.name: CurveID
objects.description: The ID of the Well Log Curve

objects.name: CurveQuality
objects.description: The Quality of the Log Curve.

objects.name: CurveUnit
objects.description: Unit of Measure for the Log Curve

objects.name: CurveVersion
objects.description: The Version of the Log Curve.

objects.name: DataSourceOrganisationID
objects.description: The main source of the header information.

objects.name: DateStamp
objects.description: Date curve was created in the database

objects.name: DaylightSavingTimeEndDate
objects.description: Day light saving end date.

objects.name: DaylightSavingTimeStartDate
objects.description: Day light saving start date.

objects.name: DefaultVerticalCRSID
objects.description: The default vertical coordinate reference system used in the vertical measurements for a well or wellbore if absent from input vertical measurements and there is no other recourse for obtaining a valid CRS.

objects.name: DefaultVerticalMeasurementID
objects.description: The default datum reference point, or zero depth point, used to determine other points vertically in a well.  References an entry in the VerticalMeasurements array.

objects.name: DefaultVerticalMeasurementID
objects.description: The default datum reference point, or zero depth point, used to determine other points vertically in a wellbore.  References an entry in the Vertical Measurements array of this wellbore.

objects.name: DefinitiveTrajectoryID
objects.description: SRN of Wellbore Trajectory which is considered the authoritative or preferred version.

objects.name: DepthCoding
objects.description: DEPRECATED: Replaced by boolean data.IsRegular. The Coding of the depth.

objects.name: DepthUnit
objects.description: DEPRECATED: use the meta[] to specify the sampling UnitOfMeasure (AbstractMetaItem of kind "Unit"; propertyNames["TopMeasuredDepth", "BottomMeasuredDepth"]). Originally: Unit of Measure for Top and Base depth.

objects.name: DisputedIndicator
objects.description: Indicates whether the GeoPolitical entity has a disputed status.

objects.name: DrillingFluidProperty
objects.description: Type of mud at time of logging (oil, water based,...)

objects.name: DrillingReasons
objects.description: The history of drilling reasons of the wellbore.

objects.name: EffectiveDate
objects.description: The date and time at which a given geopolitical entity becomes effective.

objects.name: EffectiveDate
objects.description: Date when a Prospect goes into effect.

objects.name: EffectiveDate
objects.description: The date and time at which a given organisation becomes effective.

objects.name: EffectiveDate
objects.description: Date when a Play goes into effect.

objects.name: EffectiveDate
objects.description: The date and time at which a given field becomes effective.

objects.name: FacilityEvents
objects.description: A list of key facility events.

objects.name: FacilityID
objects.description: A system-specified unique identifier of a Facility.

objects.name: FacilityName
objects.description: Name of the Facility.

objects.name: FacilityNameAliases
objects.description: DEPRECATED: please use data.NameAliases. Alternative names, including historical, by which this facility is/has been known.

objects.name: FacilityOperators
objects.description: The history of operator organizations of the facility.

objects.name: FacilitySpecifications
objects.description: facilitySpecification maintains the specification like slot name, wellbore drilling permit number, rig name etc.

objects.name: FacilityStates
objects.description: The history of life cycle states the facility has been through.

objects.name: FacilityTypeID
objects.description: The definition of a kind of capability to perform a business function or a service.

objects.name: Field
objects.description: A mineral deposit that has been exploited for commercial purposes.

objects.name: FieldDescription
objects.description: A textual description of the field.

objects.name: FieldID
objects.description: Native identifier from a Master Data Management System or other trusted source external to OSDU - stored here in order to allow for multi-system connection and synchronization. If used, the "Source" property should identify that source system.

objects.name: FieldName
objects.description: The name of the field, which may or may not coincide with a hydrocarbon field.

objects.name: FieldNameAliases
objects.description: DEPRECATED: please use data.NameAliases. Alternative names, including historical, by which this field entity is/has been known

objects.name: FrameIdentifier
objects.description: For multi-frame or multi-section files, this identifier defines the source frame in the file. If the identifier is an index number the index starts with zero and is converted to a string for this property.

objects.name: GeoPoliticalEntity
objects.description: A named geographical area which is defined and administered by an official entity.

objects.name: GeoPoliticalEntityID
objects.description: Native identifier from a Master Data Management System or other trusted source external to OSDU - stored here in order to allow for multi-system connection and synchronization. If used, the "Source" property should identify that source system.

objects.name: GeoPoliticalEntityName
objects.description: Name of the geopolitical entity.

objects.name: GeoPoliticalEntityNameAliases
objects.description: DEPRECATED: please use data.NameAliases. Alternative names, including historical, by which this geopolitical entity is/has been known.

objects.name: GeoPoliticalEntityTypeID
objects.description: Type of geopolitical entity.

objects.name: GeographicBottomHoleLocation
objects.description: The bottom hole location of the wellbore denoted by a specified geographic horizontal coordinate reference system (Horizontal CRS), such as WGS84, NAD27, or ED50. If both GeographicBottomHoleLocation and ProjectedBottomHoleLocation properties are populated on this wellbore, they must identify the same point, just in different CRSs.

objects.name: HoleTypeLogging
objects.description: Description of the hole related type of logging - POSSIBLE VALUE : OpenHole / CasedHole / CementedHole

objects.name: InitialOperatorID
objects.description: A initial operator organization ID; the organization ID may also be found in the FacilityOperatorOrganisationID of the FacilityOperator array providing the actual dates.

objects.name: InterestTypeID
objects.description: Pre-defined reasons for interest in the well or information about the well.

objects.name: InternalOrganisationIndicator
objects.description: Indicates if the organisation is internal to the enterprise.

objects.name: Interpolate
objects.description: Whether curve can be interpolated or not

objects.name: InterpreterName
objects.description: The name of person who interpreted this Log Curve.

objects.name: IsProcessed
objects.description: Indicates if the curve has been (pre)processed or if it is a raw recording

objects.name: IsRegular
objects.description: Boolean property indicating the sampling mode of the ReferenceCurveID. True means all reference curve values are regularly spaced (see SamplingInterval); false means irregular or discrete sample spacing.

objects.name: KickOffWellbore
objects.description: This is a pointer to the parent wellbore. The wellbore that starts from top has no parent.

objects.name: LogActivity
objects.description: Log Activity, used to describe the type of pass such as Calibration Pass - Main Pass - Repeated Pass

objects.name: LogCurveBusinessValueID
objects.description: The related record id of the Log Curve Business Value Type.

objects.name: LogCurveFamilyID
objects.description: The related record id of the Log Curve Family - which is the detailed Geological Physical Quantity Measured - such as neutron porosity

objects.name: LogCurveMainFamilyID
objects.description: The related record id of the Log Curve Main Family Type - which is the Geological Physical Quantity measured - such as porosity.

objects.name: LogCurveTypeID
objects.description: The related record id of the Log Curve Type - which is the standard mnemonic chosen by the company - OSDU provides an initial list

objects.name: LogRun
objects.description: Log Run - describe the run of the log - can be a number, but may be also a alphanumeric description such as a version name

objects.name: LogServiceDateInterval
objects.description: An interval built from two nested values : StartDate and EndDate. It applies to the whole log services and may apply to composite logs as [start of the first run job] and [end of the last run job]Log Service Date

objects.name: LogSource
objects.description: OSDU Native Log Source - will be updated for later releases - not to be used yet

objects.name: LogVersion
objects.description: Log Version

objects.name: LoggingDirection
objects.description: Specifies whether curves were collected downward or upward

objects.name: LoggingService
objects.description: Logging Service - mainly a short concatenation of the names of the tools

objects.name: Mnemonic
objects.description: The Mnemonic of the Log Curve is the value as received either from Raw Providers or from Internal Processing team

objects.name: NullValue
objects.description: Indicates that there is no measurement within the curve

objects.name: NumberOfColumns
objects.description: The number of columns present in this Curve for a single reference value. For simple logs this is typically 1; for image logs this holds the number of image traces or property series. Further information about the columns can be obtained via the respective log or curve APIs of the Domain Data Management Service.

objects.name: OSDU System Properties
objects.description: System properties to be injected at root level by the OsduSchemaComposer script.

objects.name: OperatingEnvironmentID
objects.description: Identifies the Facility's general location as being onshore vs. offshore.

objects.name: Organisation
objects.description: A legal or administrative body, institution, or company, or any of its divisions.

objects.name: OrganisationDescription
objects.description: Textual description of the nature of the organisation.

objects.name: OrganisationID
objects.description: Native identifier from a Master Data Management System or other trusted source external to OSDU - stored here in order to allow for multi-system connection and synchronization. If used, the "Source" property should identify that source system.

objects.name: OrganisationName
objects.description: Text which identifies an organisation.

objects.name: OrganisationNameAliases
objects.description: DEPRECATED: please use data.NameAliases. Alternative names, including historical, by which this organisation entity is/has been known.

objects.name: OrganisationPurposeDescription
objects.description: The reason why the organization was formed.

objects.name: OrganisationTypeID
objects.description: Category the organisational structure fits into. Possible values - Operating Unit, Operating sub Unit, A Business, A Department, Government Agency, etc.

objects.name: ParentBasinID
objects.description: Identifier of the parent Basin

objects.name: ParentGeoPoliticalEntityID
objects.description: The identifier of the parent GeoPoliticalEntity, for example the GeoPoliticalEntity Texas has parent ID representing the GeoPoliticalEntity USA

objects.name: PassNumber
objects.description: Indicates if the Pass is the Main one (1) or a repeated one - and it's level repetition

objects.name: Play
objects.description: A named area that likely contains a combination of certain geological factors making it prospective for mineral exploration. It is often considered to be a set of prospects with a common set of characteristics.

objects.name: PlayDescription
objects.description: Textual description about a Play.

objects.name: PlayID
objects.description: Native identifier from a Master Data Management System or other trusted source external to OSDU - stored here in order to allow for multi-system connection and synchronization. If used, the "Source" property should identify that source system.

objects.name: PlayName
objects.description: Preferred name for a Play.

objects.name: PlayNameAliases
objects.description: DEPRECATED: please use data.NameAliases. Set of alternative names for a Play.

objects.name: PlayTypeID
objects.description: The type of play as defined in PlayType.

objects.name: PrimaryMaterialID
objects.description: The primary material injected/produced from the wellbore.

objects.name: ProjectedBottomHoleLocation
objects.description: The bottom hole location of the wellbore denoted by a projected horizontal coordinate reference system (Horizontal CRS), such a UTM zone. 'Projected' in this property does not mean 'planned' or 'projected-to-bit'. If both GeographicBottomHoleLocation and ProjectedBottomHoleLocation properties are populated on this wellbore, they must identify the same point, just in different CRSs.

objects.name: Prospect
objects.description: A named area or location, likely containing commercial deposits of a mineral, that is a candidate for extraction.  This normally means a candidate drilling location..

objects.name: ProspectDescription
objects.description: Textual description about a Prospect.

objects.name: ProspectFlag
objects.description: Indicator showing whether the basin is considered prospective for hydrocarbons

objects.name: ProspectID
objects.description: Native identifier from a Master Data Management System or other trusted source external to OSDU - stored here in order to allow for multi-system connection and synchronization. If used, the "Source" property should identify that source system.

objects.name: ProspectName
objects.description: Preferred name for a Prospect, which may or may not coincide with a well or field.

objects.name: ProspectNameAliases
objects.description: DEPRECATED: please use data.NameAliases. Set of alternative names for a Prospect.

objects.name: ProspectTypeID
objects.description: The type of prospect as defined in ProspectType.

objects.name: ReferenceCurveID
objects.description: The data.Curves[].CurveID, which holds the primary index (reference) values.

objects.name: SamplingDomainTypeID
objects.description: The sampling domain, e.g. measured depth, true vertical, travel-time, calendar-time.

objects.name: SamplingInterval
objects.description: For regularly sampled curves this property holds the sampling interval. For non regular sampling rate this property is not set. The IsRegular flag indicates whether SamplingInterval is required.

objects.name: SamplingStart
objects.description: The start value/first value of the ReferenceCurveID, typically the start depth of the logging.

objects.name: SamplingStop
objects.description: The stop value/last value of the ReferenceCurveID, typically the end depth of the logging.

objects.name: SeismicReferenceElevation
objects.description: Populated only if the WellLog represents time-depth relationships or checkshots. It is expressed via the standard AbstractFacilityVerticalMeasurement. The following properties are expected to be present: VerticalMeasurementPathID (typically elevation), VerticalMeasurementTypeID as SeismicReferenceDatum, VerticalMeasurement holding the offset to either the VerticalCRSID or the chained VerticalReferenceID in the parent Wellbore.

objects.name: SequenceNumber
objects.description: A number that indicates the order in which wellbores were drilled.

objects.name: ServiceCompanyID
objects.description: The relationship to a Service Company, typically the producer or logging contractor.

objects.name: TargetFormation
objects.description: The Formation of interest for which the Wellbore is drilled to interact with. The Wellbore may terminate in a lower formation if the requirement is to drill through the entirety of the target formation, therefore this is not necessarily the Formation at TD.

objects.name: TerminationDate
objects.description: The date and time at which a given geopolitical entity is no longer in effect.

objects.name: TerminationDate
objects.description: Date when a Prospect is no longer in effect.

objects.name: TerminationDate
objects.description: The date and time at which a given organisation is no longer in effect.

objects.name: TerminationDate
objects.description: Date when a Play is no longer in effect.

objects.name: TerminationDate
objects.description: The date and time at which a given field is no longer in effect.

objects.name: ToolStringDescription
objects.description: Tool String Description - a long concatenation of the tools used for logging services such as GammaRay+NeutronPorosity

objects.name: TopDepth
objects.description: DEPRECATED: populate data.SamplingStart or data.SamplingStop instead, for informational purposes data.TopMeasuredDepth. SamplingStart and SamplingStop support other domains than depth.

objects.name: TopMeasuredDepth
objects.description: Informational Top Measured Depth of the Well Log. Always populate SamplingStart and SamplingStop, which represents the real sampling of the WellLog, including  non-depth sampling.

objects.name: TrajectoryTypeID
objects.description: Describes the predominant shapes the wellbore path can follow if deviated from vertical. Sample Values: Horizontal, Vertical, Directional.

objects.name: VerticalMeasurement
objects.description: The vertical measurement reference for the log curves, which defines the vertical reference datum for the logged depths. Either VerticalMeasurement or VerticalMeasurementID are populated.

objects.name: VerticalMeasurementID
objects.description: The ID for a distinct vertical measurement within the Wellbore VerticalMeasurements array so that it may be referenced by other vertical measurements if necessary.

objects.name: VerticalMeasurementID
objects.description: The ID for a distinct vertical measurement within the Wellbore VerticalMeasurements array so that it may be referenced by other vertical measurements if necessary.

objects.name: VerticalMeasurementID
objects.description: DEPRECATED: Use data.VerticalMeasurement.VerticalReferenceID instead. References an entry in the Vertical Measurement array for the Wellbore identified by WellboreID, which defines the vertical reference datum for all curve measured depths. Either VerticalMeasurementID or VerticalMeasurement are populated.

objects.name: VerticalMeasurements
objects.description: List of all depths and elevations pertaining to the well, like, water depth, mud line elevation, etc.

objects.name: VerticalMeasurements
objects.description: List of all depths and elevations pertaining to the wellbore, like, plug back measured depth, total measured depth, KB elevation

objects.name: Well
objects.description: The origin of a set of wellbores.

objects.name: WellLog
objects.description: A well log is a data type that correlates a particular measurement or multiple measurements in a wellbore against depth and/or time within that wellbore. When plotted visually, well logs are typically long line graphs (called "curves") but may sometimes be discrete points or intervals. This schema object is intended for digital well logs, not raster log files or raster calibration files, but may be used for the latter in the absence of a defined OSDU schema for these use cases.

objects.name: WellLogTypeID
objects.description: Well Log Type short Description such as Raw; Evaluated; Composite;....

objects.name: Wellbore
objects.description: A hole in the ground extending from a point at the earth's surface to the maximum point of penetration.

objects.name: WellboreID
objects.description: The Wellbore where the Well Log Work Product Component was recorded

objects.name: ZeroTime
objects.description: Optional time reference for (calender) time logs. The ISO date time string representing zero time. Not to be confused with seismic travel time zero. The latter is defined by SeismicReferenceDatum.

objects.name: acl
objects.description: The access control tags associated with this entity.

objects.name: ancestry
objects.description: The links to data, which constitute the inputs.

objects.name: createTime
objects.description: Timestamp of the time at which initial version of this OSDU resource object was created. Set by the System. The value is a combined date-time string in ISO-8601 given in UTC.

objects.name: createUser
objects.description: The user reference, which created the first version of this resource object. Set by the System.

objects.name: id
objects.description: Previously called ResourceID or SRN which identifies this OSDU resource object without version.

objects.name: kind
objects.description: The schema identification for the OSDU resource object following the pattern {Namespace}:{Source}:{Type}:{VersionMajor}.{VersionMinor}.{VersionPatch}. The versioning scheme follows the semantic versioning, https://semver.org/.

objects.name: legal
objects.description: The entity's legal tags and compliance status. The actual contents associated with the legal tags is managed by the Compliance Service.

objects.name: meta
objects.description: The Frame of Reference meta data section linking the named properties to self-contained definitions.

objects.name: modifyTime
objects.description: Timestamp of the time at which this version of the OSDU resource object was created. Set by the System. The value is a combined date-time string in ISO-8601 given in UTC.

objects.name: modifyUser
objects.description: The user reference, which created this version of this resource object. Set by the System.

objects.name: tags
objects.description: A generic dictionary of string keys mapping to string value. Only strings are permitted as keys and values.

objects.name: version
objects.description: The version number of this OSDU resource; set by the framework.
